Question: Describe winter season in your hometown (do not disclose the name of your hometown).
Answer:
 To describe the winter season in my hometown, I can start at the beginning of the winter. In November, there can be a sudden rain fall and temperature drop. Then the winter starts. The winter can last for more than four or five months untill April of  the next year. The temperature in winter can be as low as -10 centigrade.